{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idef2970d8-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2009"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2009"},"text":"§ 2009.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this subchapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef2970d9-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2009/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “State” means each of the 50 States, the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, Guam, the Virgin Islands of the United States, American Samoa, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands, and the Federated States of Micronesia.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idef2970da-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2009/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State director","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “State director” means, with respect to a State, the Director of the Rural Economic and Community Development State Office.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idef2970db-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/128/tIII/s381A"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–128, title III, § 381A","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/tVII/s761"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, title VII, § 761","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-04"},"text":"Apr. 4, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1139"},"text":"110 Stat. 1139","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/171/tVI/s6020/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–171, title VI, § 6020(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-05-13"},"text":"May 13, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/363"},"text":"116 Stat. 363","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idef2970dc-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idef2970dd-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idef2970de-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/171"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–171","children":[],"tail":" redesignated pars. (2) and (3) as (1) and (2), respectively, and struck out heading and text of former par. (1). Text read as follows: “The terms ‘rural’ and ‘rural area’ mean, subject to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1926/a/7"},"text":"section 1926(a)(7) of this title","children":[],"tail":", a city, town, or unincorporated area that has a population of 50,000 inhabitants or less, other than an urbanized area immediately adjacent to a city, town, or unincorporated area that has a population in excess of 50,000 inhabitants.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idef2970df-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"definitions","id":"idef2970e0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Definition of Rural Areas for Certain Business and Community Facilities Programs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/78/tVII/s730"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–78, title VII, § 730","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1164"},"text":"113 Stat. 1164","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/78/tVII/s730"},"text":"“Notwithstanding section 381A of the Consolidated Farm and Rural Development Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2009"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2009","children":[],"tail":"), in fiscal year 2000 and thereafter, the definitions of rural areas for certain business programs administered by the Rural Business-Cooperative Service and the community facilities programs administered by the Rural Housing Service shall be those provided for in statute and regulations prior to the enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127"},"text":"Public Law 104–127","children":[],"tail":" ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-04"},"text":"Apr. 4, 1996","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dA/s101/a/tVII/s735"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. A, § 101(a) [title VII, § 735]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","c